      "description": "Objective: Boundary Value Analysis (BVA) for schema constraints.\n\nMethodology: Testing the database's internal logic to prevent negative financial values."
    },
    {
      "name": "2: Data Integrity (CRUD Operations)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Test 2.1: Precise Record Creation & Verification",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Step 1: Record Creation Successful\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.equal(\"success\");\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "// Strategy: Chain a request or use a snippet to verify the specific entry\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Data Type Integrity: Price is exactly 149.99\", function () {\r",
                  "    // Here we would usually follow up with a SELECT query to confirm the decimal precision\r",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n    \"query\": \"INSERT INTO products (name, price, stock) VALUES ('Mechanical Keyboard', 149.99, 50);\"\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/execute",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "execute"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Verify that the Python Bridge correctly maps data types from a JSON request to the SQL table without truncation or rounding errors."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Test 2.2: The \"Update & Reflect\" Validation",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Record Updated Successfully\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().affected_rows).to.be.at.least(1);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "// SQA Insight: Verification of State\r",
                  "/* Note: In your next SELECT call, verify that 'price' remains 149.99 \r",
                  "   while 'stock' changed to 45. This confirms 'Partial Update' integrity.\r",
                  "*/"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n    \"query\": \"UPDATE products SET stock = 45 WHERE name = 'Mechanical Keyboard';\"\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/execute",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "execute"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Ensure that an UPDATE operation doesn't accidentally alter unrelated columns (a common \"side-effect\" bug)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Test Case 2.3: Safe Deletion & Referential Integrity",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Parent Product Deleted\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Verify Cascade: Check Orders table\", function () {\r",
                  "    /* Manual SQA Step: Run SELECT * FROM orders WHERE product_id = [ID].\r",
                  "       The result should be an empty array []. \r",
                  "       If the order still exists, the 'Cascade' rule failed.\r",
                  "    */\r",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n    \"query\": \"DELETE FROM products WHERE name = 'Mechanical Keyboard';\"\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/execute",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "execute"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Ensure that an UPDATE operation doesn't accidentally alter unrelated columns (a common \"side-effect\" bug)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Focus: Positive testing of the Data Lifecycle.\n\nValidation Points:\n\n1\\. Precision: Ensuring DECIMAL types maintain accuracy.  \n2\\. Side-Effect Analysis: Ensuring updates to one column don't corrupt others.  \n3\\. Referential Integrity: Verifying that the FOREIGN KEY relationship correctly removes orphaned records."
    },
    {
      "name": "3: ACID Property Testing",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Test 3.1: Atomicity (The Rollback Test)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Transaction Rolled Back\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(400);\r",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.equal(\"Transaction Rolled Back\");\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "/* SQA Manual Check: \r",
                  "   Run SELECT * FROM orders; \r",
                  "   If Atomicity works, the order for 4999.95 should NOT be in the table.\r",
                  "*/"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n    \"queries\": [\r\n        \"INSERT INTO orders (product_id, quantity, total_price) VALUES (1, 5, 4999.95);\",\r\n        \"UPDATE products SET stock = stock - 5 WHERE p_id = 9999;\" \r\n    ]\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/transaction",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "transaction"
              ]
            },
            "description": "try to place an order, but the second part of the SQL script (updating stock) has a syntax error."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Test 3.2: Consistency (Foreign Key Constraint)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Referential Integrity Maintained\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(400);\r",
                  "    // MySQL Error 1452: Cannot add or update a child row (Foreign Key fails)\r",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().error_code).to.equal(1452);\r",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n    \"query\": \"INSERT INTO orders (product_id, quantity, total_price) VALUES (500, 1, 10.00);\"\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/execute",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "execute"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Trying to create an order for a product_id that does not exist in the products table."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Test 3.3: Isolation (Concurrency Simulation)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Isolation: Prevent Overselling\", function () {\r",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();\r",
                  "    // If stock was insufficient, no rows should be updated\r",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.affected_rows).to.equal(0);\r",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n    \"query\": \"UPDATE products SET stock = stock - 100 WHERE p_id = 1 AND stock >= 100;\"\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/execute",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "execute"
              ]
            },
            "description": "This tests if the database handles two \"hits\" at once. While we can't do full multi-threading in one Postman tab, we can test the Locking logic."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Objective: Validating the Atomicity of complex e-commerce operations.\n\nAchievement: Verified that the Python-MySQL bridge successfully performs ROLLBACK on partial failures, preventing orphaned records in the orders table.\n\nEdge Case Handling: Simulated Foreign Key violations (Error 1452) to ensure data consistency across relational tables."
    }
  ]
}